This paper is primarily focused on the detection of malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also utilizes neural networks for the detection process, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the models and the need for efficient and effective detection, which falls under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and neural networks (cs.NE).
